challenges.description:
The shader below was mechanically copy-pasted from HLSL into a GLSL file. It uses five HLSL-only built-in names that do not exist in GLSL. Find and fix all five.

Broken shader:
```
uniform vec2 u_resolution;
uniform float u_time;
out vec4 fragColor;

void main() {
    vec2 uv = gl_FragCoord.xy / u_resolution;
    float t = frac(u_time * 0.5);          // broken
    float r = saturate(uv.x * 2.0 - 0.5); // broken
    float g = lerp(0.2, 0.8, uv.y);       // broken
    float b = length(uv - vec2(0.5));
    b = saturate(1.0 - b * 2.0);          // broken
    float angle = atan2(uv.y - 0.5, uv.x - 0.5); // broken
    fragColor = vec4(r, g, b, 1.0);
}
```

